    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card_column">
      <div class="card_title">
        Go-Quads
      </div>
      <div class="card_tags">
        <span class="card_tag">Go</span>
        <span class="card_tag">Quad heaps</span>
        <span class="card_tag">Art</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card_description">
        <p class="card_description_paragraph">
          Go-Quads was my first experiment with the Go language and algorithmic art. A picture is split into four quadrants, and the average pixel color is computed for each quad. The quad with the largest error between the actual pixels and average color is split again, and pushed onto the heap. Stylistic parameters such as background colors or circular quads can be set.
        </p>
        <p class="right">
          <a href='/projects/go-quads'>Read more...</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card_image_container">
      <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/bhm-mysite/goquads.jpg" alt="Go Quads Zebra" width="100%" draggable="False"/>
    </div>
  </div>
